description: Despite Hamas leader's death, the Israeli prime minister has committed his army to a new phase of the offensive against Gaza, this time targeting the north of the Palestinian enclave, with already appalling consequences for the population.
title: Benjamin Netanyahu's new war against northern Gaza Strip

description: VP Harris described Trump's rally at Madison Square Garden as 'more vivid than usual,' President Biden called it 'simply embarrassing.' In a rare move, the Trump campaign tried to distance itself from the remarks.
title: Democrats escalate critics of Trump after comedian calls Puerto Rico 'floating island of garbage' at his NYC rally

description: The fire damaged three ballots inside, while officials say a fire at a drop box in nearby Vancouver, Washington, early Monday destroyed hundreds of ballots.
title: US elections: Police identified 'suspect vehicle' after ballot boxes set on fire in Oregon and Washington states

description: Rodri succeeded eight-time winner Lionel Messi of Argentina.
title: Football: Spaniards Rodri and Bonmatí win Ballon d'Or award for best men's and women's players in the world

description: Tens of thousands of people gathered in Tblisi to denounce the weekend's parliamentary election, which the country's president and international election observers have alleged was rigged.
title: Georgians protest contested election results

description: Passed 92-10, the bill would effectively prevents the UN Palestinian refugee agency, which Israeli leaders have accused of having ties to Hamas, from operating in Israel and East Jerusalem, halting essential services such as cleaning, education, and healthcare.
title: Israeli parliament approves ban on UNRWA in Israel

description: South Africa, which brought the case before the International Court of Justice, arguing that the Gaza war has breached Israel's legal obligations, filed a document allegedly containing over 4,000 exhibits and annexes.
title: Gaza: South Africa files 'evidence' for their 'genocide' case against Israel

description: The dual national had been detained since 2020, and had been convicted of playing a role in a 2008 mosque bombing in the southern city of Shiraz, as an alleged leader of the Tondar group, which reportedly aims to topple Iran's government.
title: Iran executes German-Iranian Jamshid Sharmahd

description: Judge Reuben Nyakundi convicted Peter Ushuru Khalumi and David Ekai Lokere of murdering a Kenyan-born Ugandan Olympian, distance runner Benjamin Kiplagat, in case that had shocked the country.
title: Kenyan court finds two men guilty of murdering Olympian runner

description: In the swing state of Pennsylvania, Democratic prosecutor Larry Krasner sued the Trump-aligned billionaire, over his contentious lottery-style giveaways to registered voters, which he had been warned may violate federal law.
title: Elon Musk sued over $1 million giveaways

description: 'Strava Leaks' (2/3). Three of the world's most important leaders have been put in danger due to their security guards' use of the sports social media app Strava. In this second episode, we reveal how the current and former US presidents' lives are put in danger by the not-so-secret lives of Secret Service agents.
title: Biden and Trump put in danger by Secret Service agents: Watch the second episode of StravaLeaks

description: Amid a tense geopolitical climate, marked by Macron's July approval of Morocco's autonomy plan for the disputed Western Sahara and migration rows between Paris and Rabat, Macron's visit serves to mend diplomatic ties, despite tensions with Algeria.
title: Macron visits Morocco for a diplomatic reset

description: Michel Barnier's office said the operation 'went very well' and that the 73-year-old had returned to work.
title: French PM Barnier operated for 'cervical lesion'

description: To understand the social repercussions of criminalizing abortion in some US states, photographer Stacy Kranitz, commissioned by the investigative media ProPublica, documented Maryon York Hollis's life for over a year, who was denied an abortion despite the risks to her and her child.
title: A year in the life of a devastated Tennesse family after a prevented abortion

description: Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba suffered a parliamentary election defeat on October 27, partly due to rising prices, especially of ramen, after three decades of deflation. Economic columnist Philippe Escande believes that this shift could be a positive sign.
title: 'The Japanese PM's electoral defeat was tied to rising inflation, symbolized by ramen'

description: During Emmanuel Macron's first state visit to Morocco from Monday, October 28 to Wednesday, October 30, multiple agreements and partnerships are due to be signed, including in the energy sector.
title: In Morocco, French companies have great economic ambitions

description: After a rocky start to the season left the 20-time English champions sitting 14th in the Premier League, the club's new leadership grew dissatisfied with the slow pace of change under the Dutch manager.
title: Manchester United sack manager Erik ten Hag

description: The country notably invoked its strict rules on secularism to ban its athletes from wearing religious symbols, including the hijab, during the Paris 2024 Olympics.
title: France's hijab bans in sports is 'discriminatory,' say UN experts

description: In just over three weeks, the Israeli army has killed hundreds of Palestinians in the enclave's far north, as it seeks to empty the area of its inhabitants. Some 60,000 people were driven from their homes. Those who remain are abandoned to their fate.
title: Israel continues assault on ravaged northern Gaza Strip

description: Fanny Lauby, political scientist and associate professor of political science at Montclair State University in New Jersey, answered readers' questions about the importance of immigration in the electorate and in the platforms of the two White House candidates.
title: Fanny Lauby, political scientist: 'Trump's plan to deport undocumented immigrants would deal a fatal blow to the US economy'

description: Africans are being trapped by cartels, lured by the promise of lucrative customer service contracts, and forced into laboring in centers devoted to cyberfraud across Myanmar, Laos and Cambodia.

description: The Republican candidate held a rally in the legendary Manhattan venue on Sunday. With his guests, some of whom made overtly racist remarks, he delivered his aggressive rhetoric, escalating his attacks on the Democratic candidate, Kamala Harris.

description: On October 20, 1984, Maison Cartier inaugurated a site dedicated to contemporary art in Jouy-en-Josas, southwest of Paris. Through a series of ground-breaking exhibitions, the Fondation Cartier shone the spotlight on promising unknown and established artists.

description: Yamandu Orsi and Alvaro Delgado beat out nine other candidates bidding to replace Lacalle Pou, who has a 50% approval rating but is barred from seeking a second consecutive five-year term.
title: Uruguay's left, center-right candidates to duel in presidential runoff next month

description: On Monday, the LDP's election committee chief, former premier Junichiro Koizumi's son Shinjiro Koizumi, resigned. The most likely next step is that Ishiba will now seek to head a minority government, with the divided opposition seen as probably incapable of forming a coalition of their own, analysts said.
title: Japan PM under pressure after debacle election

description: Located close to Hezbollah installations, the plant, which has been repeatedly hit by explosions, is now operating at a very low level.
title: South of Beirut, Sainte-Thérèse hospital under constant threat from Israeli bombs

description: A hiking trail created in 2023 will take you around the Charente-Maritime island. Spend five days exploring beaches, vineyards and forests, while watching the tides and the greylag geese.

description: Donald Trump accused Kamala Harris on Sunday of destroying the United States. Several other speakers at the 20,000-seat Madison Square Garden venue drew cheers with their barbs against Harris, Puerto Rico and Latinos in the final stretch of one of America's closest-ever White House races.
title: Trump's New York rally draws criticism as he ramps up Harris attacks with wife Melania present

description: By forcing public employees to hand over their passports in the workplace, the Communist Party is strengthening its grip on society. Many citizens are questioning the justifications for this control.
title: Teachers, doctors, civil servants and bankers: Foreign travel of Chinese citizens tightly controlled by CCP

description: After Monaco lost their first match of the season, Paris Saint-Germain, who beat Marseille at the Stade Velodrome on Sunday, moved into the top spot of Ligue 1.
title: PSG clinch top spot after 3-0 win over Marseille: 'We dedicate this victory to the fans'
